how did you pray when you were a child how do you pray different now i prayed kneeling by my bed with my eyes shut and my hands folded out loud with my mother nearby i prayed for all my family pets school and whatever was happening at the time now i pray silently after i'm in bed eyes shut try not to fall asleep before i'm done for all my family friends whatever's happening at the time and for jesus to come soon well when i was little i didn't really understand god i thought he was like santa like if i pray for something like a barbie house or something i would get it now i pray for people who are sick are going through a hard time or people who don't know god yet i also pray to thank god for everything i have we americans can take our things for granted way to easily i laughed when i read try not to fall asleep before i'm done i had the same problem now i just pray with the light on then turn it off when i'm done so i don't fall asleep lol Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Book of Isaiah Shaggy dog story Philosophical skepticism The Amber Spyglass Prayer Mass (liturgy) Spidey Super Stories Rich Mullins Sant Thakar Singh Ayyavazhi mythology John the Baptist The Catcher in the Rye Mojave people Characters of The Sandman 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Night (book) EastEnders Milton H. Erickson Out-of-body experience Mary, the mother of Jesus Free will Horus Time Out of Mind Faustyna Kowalska John Lennon Hansel und Gretel The Shining (film) Social rule Church of Christ, Scientist John Howard Yoder Cliff Richard Muslim ibn Aqeel Tridentine Mass She Loves You The Subtle Knife Dream Eastern Orthodox Church Sermon on the Mount Otello Humphrey Bogart Priesthood (Mormonism) Joseph of Arimathea Predestination Prayer in Christianity Edgar Cayce Threads (Stargate SG-1) Amidah Sleep A Course In Miracles The Critic Mother Teresa The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Shakers Blankets (graphic novel) Religious Society of Friends One Piece minor characters Elvis Presley Th